<h1 class="govuk-heading-xl page-heading">Cookies</h1>
<p>
    This service puts small files known as cookies onto your computer to collect information about how you browse the site.
</p>
<p>
    Cookies are used to:
</p>
<ul class="govuk-list">
    <li>measure what you do on the site so it can be improved </li>
    <li>remember the notifications you’ve seen so we don’t show them to you again</li>
</ul>

<p>
    Find out more about <a class="govuk-link" rel="external noopener noreferrer" href="http://www.aboutcookies.org/">how to manage cookies.</a>
</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Cookies that measure website use</h2>
<p>
    We use Google Analytics software to collect information about how you use the site.
</p>
<p>
    Google Analytics stores information about:
</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
    <li>the pages you visit</li>
    <li>how long you spend on each page</li>
    <li>how you got to the site</li>
    <li>what you click on while you’re visiting</li>
</ul>

<p>
    We don’t collect or store your personal information (for example your name or address) so this information can’t be used to identify who you are. And we don’t allow Google to use or share our analytics data.
</p>

